                    INSTITUTE FOR SYSTEMS ANALYSIS<BR>
 
         9, Prospect 60-let  Octyabria, 117312 Moscow, Russia<BR>
             Tel. 135 50 43 office  Fax: (095) 938 22 09<BR>
                    EM: <vtsygichko@glas.apc.org><BR>

 Prof. Vitaly Tsygichko, prof.Dmitry Chereshkin,prof.Georgy Smolian.</CENTER><BR>
 

<P>     The quantitative  estimations of efficiency for information security systems (ISS) are still important and very difficult problem.  Our team are working in this sphere for a long time.  There is the general
idea of our approach in this paper.</P>
<P>    By "The  Information Security System" (ISS) we shall mean organization for combine efforts different means and ways of  counteraction to threats  for information security.</P>
<P>       Functional structure ISS.</P>
 <P>    We shall present functional structure of ISS as hierarchical System, consisting of parts of different levels which shone on the picture. As you can see on the picture,  the structure of ISS is defined by
structure of possible threats. As you know each threat has same different ways of realization.  For example, a plunder of information my be make by different manners.  In correspondence with this possible  manners we design the structure of the ISS.</P>
     <P>Elementary part the ISS (first level) is some means of counteraction to a concrete way of realization concrete threat.</P>
     <P>The parts  of the second level provide organization and coordination of  actions  for  all means of counteraction to determined way of realization of threat.</P>
     <P>The parts of the third  level  coordinate the actions of all means of counteraction to all various ways of realizations of each threat.</P>
     <P>The parts of the fourth level coordinate the actions of  parts  of the third level against all prospective threats.</P>
     <P>The the fifth level coordinate actions of parts of the fourth level for maintenance information security for all objects which enter in the ISS.</P>
     <P>The process of functioning any ISS can be presented in the  terms of this hierarchical structure.
      Statement of a problems.</P>
     <P>In a general kind of the problem of an estimation of  effici ency may be present through three tasks:
     To define efficiency of functioning the ISS in question by a presence complex of means for maintenance information security;</P>
     </P>To define  structure the ISS in question ensuring minimum it cost at a given level information security of object;</P>
     <P>To define  structure  the ISS in question ensuring maximum level of information security for object at given size of resources.</P>
     <P>The main idea of our approach basis on two principles.</P>
     <P>At first,  all calculations of efficiency are made from first level to highest level of the ISS. For this We mast have all information for elementary part of first level of the ISS in question.</P>
     <P>The second principle is the principle equiprotection.  This principle supposes that estimation of efficiency of the ISS is equally efficiency of most weak part of this ISS.</P>
     <P>By central  concept ,  allowing us to construct normative base of quantitative estimations  of efficiency the ISS is specific efficiency of a means.  It is "Counteractions to a particular way of  realization of threat  "  for  all elementary part of first level of the ISS.  The specific efficiency can be interpreted as probability that  the  given way realization of threat will be prevented .</P>
    <P>The dimensional  representation  of  this parameters defined distinctions of functioning each means of protection.  It can be size  of protected  territory by one means in unit time.  Quantity of the coded
information by one means in unit time or volume of the  processed  information by one means in unit time and etc..</P>
     <P>In correspondence with principle of equiprotection,  we shall enter criterion RELIABILITY of PROTECTION - Qjkl, as universal criterion of  efficiency for all parts and all level of ISS,  beginning from the
second level.</P>
    <P> In this case Reliability of protection of object  on  the  second level from  j-way of k-threat is defined by expression</P>
 <PRE>
               Qjk = 1 - [Pjk * (1 - Ujk)      (1) ,
 
   where:
    Pjk  - dependence  of  probability   of realization j-way 
            of k-threat from a degree of protection - Ujk,
    Ujk - degree of protection of object from j-way of k-threat.
    Pjk = Pjk(Ujk)
 </PRE>
     <P>The dependence Pjk(Ujk) fixes obvious fact,  than the more effective protection so less the probability of threats realization.  There is very difficult problem to define this function. We have same different methods for defining  this dependence and for calculations efficiency elementary part of means of counteractions.  Same of this methods and models are very complex.</P>
    <P> The expression (1) is a basis for calculation parameters of efficiency of measures of counteraction at all following levels of theISS.</P>
    <P> The purpose of activity of the third level is maintained equiprotection of  object from all ways of realization of the threat in question.</P>
 <P>The reliability of protection for third level is defined  formula (2)</P>
 <PRE>
    Qk = Qjk min from { Qjk} for all j(J    (2).
 </PRE>
<P>The purpose  of functioning of the fourth level the ISS is maintenance
equiprotection of object from all threats. It means, that criterion of
efficiency  for this level is equal to the minimum reliability protection on the third level.</P>
 <PRE>
 Ql =  Qkl min from  {Qkl} = Qjkl from {Qjkl} For all jkl (JKL. (3)
 </PRE>
  <P>   The purpose of functioning the ISS as  integrity  is  maintenance
equalreliability  of  protection  all objects in view of their gravity
-Bl. Criterion of efficiency of functioning the ISS is defined by formula</P>
 <PRE>
    Qiss = [Ql * Bl}min from {Ql * Bl} for all l(L     (4).
 </PRE>
<P>     As you  can see this approach allows us to formulate the problems
of an estimation of efficiency existing  the ISS and on the basis of it decisions  to put problems of creation new ISS or modernization existing one. It allows us to carry out research and comparative analyses  different ISS  on  critical  parameters  and to reveal perspective way of their development.</P>
<P>     This approach  was implemented by the mathematical model which was used for practical  calculations.</P>

