<tr>
<td width=440>

<P>Dear OSS Viewer,</P>

<P>We are pleased to present to you the final schedule for the GBI conference,
a one-day affiliated conference at OSS'96!</P>

<P>Take care and have a good day,</P>

<P>Zhi</P>

<P>GLOBAL BUSINESS INTELLIGENCE '96</P>

A One Day Affiliated Conference at OSS '96<BR>
September 18, Wednesday  9:00 AM to 5:00 PM<BR>
Registration from 8:00 AM<BR>
Sheraton Premiere Hotel, Tysons Corner, Virginia<BR>

<P>Morning Workshop: The Threat Posed to Company's Intellectual Property by the
Operations of Business Intelligence Departments .....and, What You Can Do
About It!</P>

<P>Competitive intelligence is the fastest growing profession in the business
world today.  The Society of competitive Intelligence Professionals (SCIP)
boasts some 4,000 members worldwide in over 35 countries.  Ninety percent
(90%) of the Fortune 500 are represented and international chapters are
located in Mexico, Japan, Australia, China, and most European countries.
SCIP members pride themselves in conducting their operations legally and
ethically - and, their skills as well as successes are growing surprisingly
well.  Their success is due in large part because their operations go
undetected in most companies and even when they are, because of their
"legal" nature, company security can do little about it.</P>

<P>This workshop - led by three of the world's leading experts on this subject
- will provide the attendees with an insightful understanding of this new
intelligence threat and advice and guidelines on how companies should go
about protecting their intellectual property from this growing, worldwide
threat.</P>

<P>Global Business Intelligence: Operations, Threats, and Countermeasures</P>

<UL>*  Business Intelligence Operations - Jan P. Herring, former Director BI
for Motorola, Inc and NIO for S&T.

*  The BI Threat to Companies - Bill DeGenaro, former head BI for 3M and
Director CI Strategy for DoD</UL>

<UL>*  Countering this New Intelligence Threat - Ed O'Malley, former VP for
MCI's Systems Integrity Group  and Director Counterintelligence for the FBI</UL>

<P>Please call Jan P. Herring at 860.232.4420 for more program details.</P>

<P>Afternoon Session:</P>

<UL>*  Cyber-Crime: New Methods for Electronic theft and Extortion - Ira
Winkler, National Computer Security Association and Winn Schwartau, author,
INFORMATION WARFARE: Chaos on the Electronic Superhighway and The Complete
Internet Business Toolkit</UL>

<UL>*  Case studies in Detecting and Stopping Industrial Espionage - Tatiana
Gau, Executive Vice President, PARVUS</UL>

<UL>*  Intellectual Property Law: Present Weaknesses, Future Directions - Brian
Kahin, Esq., Director,  Intellectual Property Program, Harvard JFK</UL>

<UL>* National Information Strategy and CEO Effectiveness: Recommendations -
Robert Steele, President, OPEN SOURCE SOLUTIONS, Inc.</UL>

Cost:  Corporate $300; Government $200; Academic $100.<BR>
Conference is free to full participants in OSS '96.<BR>
For complete OSS '96 schedule and registration:<BR>
Email <A HREF="MAILTO:OSS96@oss.net">OSS96@oss.net</a>. Fax (703) 242-1711, or Call (703) 242-1700<BR>

<P>To register for GBI '96 with credit card payment, fax completed form to
(703) 242-1711;</P>
<P>To register for GBI '96 with check payment, make check payable to OSS, Inc.
and mail with completed registration form to: OSS '96, 11005 Langton Arms
Court, Oakton, VA 22124-1807</P>

Zhi Hamby-Nye, President<BR>
Real Trends, Inc.<BR>

