<H2><Center>
Hacker Alert!  Don't miss this! OSS'96
</H2>
</Center>
<BR>
Hacker alert.  <BR>
<P>OSS '96, the annual gathering of spies,
librarians, military and law enforcement analysts, and
the occasional corporate electronic security person, is
offering free seats for up to ten hackers endorsed by
Emmanuel Goldstein, Erik Bloodaxe, Rop Gonggrijp, or
Glenn Tenney, as bona fide.  Get a free ride (costs
corporation $1000) and come hear and challenge people
like Ira Winkler from NCSA (on his billion dollar heist),
Paul Strassmann (on informatoin terrorism and information
crime), and so on.  For a complete copy of the program,
send blank email to <OSS96@oss.net>.  Check out our Web
site at <a href="http://www.oss.net">http://www.oss.net</a>, or send email directly to
Robert D. Steele (keynote speaker at many hacker 
cons, coined the phrase "hackers are a national resource
because they show us the emperor is naked"), at
<a href="MAILTO:ceo@oss.net">ceo@oss.net</a>.  Rise up!  Come strut your righteous stuff.
Hotel rooms can be made available.</P>


