<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<img border=0 width=43 height=43 src="../../images/hack.gif">
</td>
<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h2>


</h2>


</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>


<H2><Center>
Examples of Social Engineering
</H2>
</Center>
<I>These are transcripts of some social engineering tapes made by hackers as a demonstration of what they can do. Note that the phone personnel give out codes and passwords. Example #3 is particularly interesting.</I>

<H4>Example #1</H4>

(name blanked)  Female Voice</P>

<P>Hello?</P>

<P>Can I help you?</P>

<P>Hey.....Hows it going?</P>

<P>OK.</P>
<P>Hows it going? This is Bill over at Bell Atlantic Social Engineering.  How ya doing?</P>
<P>All right.</P>
<P>Hey you got the number.... Do you have the number for SCC overthere?  Its not 9828381 is it?</P>
<P>(hesitate...)  ...No.   Network Test Center?</P>
<P>Yeh...they probably...</P>
<P>205</P>
<P>Oh...Hold on..205</P>
<P>Ah...-4005   Area Code 703.</P>
<P>Yeh.  Thats right  I forgot they moved.  They used to be 9828381.</P>
<P>Uh huh</P>
<P>Ah hhhh right. Thanks a lot for your help.</P>
<P>Bye bye.</P>
<P>mmm</P>


<H4>Example #2</H4>
<P>Male Voice answers......</P>
<P>Where have I reached?</P>
<P>Network ah...Technical Team</P>
<P>I guess if forwarded from 205-4005 to you guys....You guys handle Vienna?</P>
<P>Yeh...Actually this is 205-4005.</P>
<P>You guys do handle Vienna right?</P>
<P>Right.</P>
<P>Ok..got a number here were been trying to test...need ya to go ahead and put three way on it so we can test it.</P>
<P>Ah.....well,  is it an order???</P>
<P>(Background noise.....man speaking....well thats interesting)</P>
<P>Well, you see what happened was they had it put on then it wasnt working.  So they had it  took it off, ...They had it taken off....they started bitching....so we just want it tested so we know everything is working with it...I just need you to go ahead and add it so we can test it.</P>
<P>What is the phone number?</P>
<P>Whats the phone number?  (Speaking to someone in background)  Man gives number...876-</P>
<P>876-4866   Area code 703.</P>
<P>You said it works out of Vienna?</P>
<P>Yep.  I believe thats Vienna.</P>
<P>No, thats ...</P>
<P>Vienna...Falls Church  (man in background repeats Vienna...Falls Church)</P>
<P>Actually Merrifield.</P>
<P>Merrifield.   Thats right.  And thats all in the same area.</P>
<P>And who are you?</P>
<P>This is Bill Corbett.</P>
<P>Bill Corbett...ah And where you at?</P>
<P>Special Services...</P>
<P>You up in Maryland?  (other man is speaking in background)</P>
<P>No.</P>
<P>Ah...I thought Special Services was out of Maryland now.</P>
<P>Oh yeh...Special Services is out of Maryland.  I thought you asked me if I was IN Maryland.</P>
<P>A few seconds of silence.</P>
<P>Thats where the main office is.</P>
<P>Yeh...I think they moved up there not to long ago.</P>
<P>Yes...its funny... you guys moved down to VA....we moved up to Maryland.</P>
<P>How long did you guys move down there?</P>
<P>Oh... its a couple.. three months now.</P>
<P>All right.</P>
<P>(background man talking....another several voices is added)</P>
<P>Mr. (name withheld).....Are you A type Service?</P>
<P>Yeh..thats right.</P>
<P>And Special Services is workin on it?  </P>
<P>Yeh...thats .I mean...  They had the customer bitchin about it, so they wanted us to take it out and make sure.</P>
<P>Hmmm.  Where you at now?  The customers location?</P>
<P>Yeh....thats right.  Were at the prim.</P>
<P>And you just need three way calling added to it?</P>
<P>Yeh...and if is ok we will go ahead and call you back if everything tests out.</P>
<P>Hmm.  Let me see if I can figure out what that is.....</P>
<P>What is that?  A1A?</P>
<P>5A.</P>
<P>Oh.  Whew!  I knew.that it wasn;t ..... .Is it an ESM?</P>
<P>No, thats a USOC code. </P>
<P>Oh- all right.</P>
<P>Its not what we use in the office.</P>
<P>(voices heard in background again)</P>
<P>(Several seconds of silence.  Computer keys clicking on the other end from phone company)</P>
<P>Are you on-line now?</P>
<P>Excuse me?</P>
<P>Are you talking on that line now?</P>
<P>No.</P>
<P>Ok. I was gonna say you can try a three way conversation if you wanto.</P>
<P>Oh - OK.  The  feature is added though?</P>
<P>Yeh.</P>
<P>All right.  Well go ahead and test it.  Thanks a lot for  your help.</P>
<P>All right man.</P>
<P>Bye Bye.</P>


<H4>Example #3</H4>
<P>This is (name blanked).  Can I have your area code and telephone number please?</P>
<P>Hi Steve.  How ya doin? </P>
<P>Good.</P>
<P> This is Ron Contour over at Sprint Social Engineering.  How ya doin?</P>
<P>Good Ron.</P>
<P>Hey.  Is CIS up for you guys over there?</P>
<P>It is.</P>
<P>All right.  Ah... Oh no.... I think its coming up now over here.</P>
<P>Were you all down? Or..</P>
<P>Well, it was down over here.</P>
<P>Ah..... actually its coming up so I wont even waste your time.  I am going to go ahead an do this myself. Thanks anyway.</P>
<P>Weve had a good day with CIS though ..</P>
<P>Oh- have you.</P>
<P>Yeh.. today.</P>
<P>No way!</P>
<P>Well, yesterday was our bad day.</P>
<P>Actually man.....its not even coming up over here.  Ah.  Ok.   It looks like youll have to help me out anyway.</P>
<P>What ya got?</P>
<P>I got an account number here.  I just need to see if you ah...show it in the system or not.</P>
<P>OK.</P>
<P>OK.  What I actually   Acutally, What I  need here first cause I tried to do this yesterday and wasnt able to.  Couldnt find information.</P>
<P>OK</P>
<P>Do you have the number for the CNA that handles area code 313?</P>
<P>Let me get it.</P>
<P>All right.</P>
<P>Also, we have been having problems with data loss between CIS and the switch which likes really sucks.</P>
<P>Dont tell me those things....(jokingly)  I dont want to hear those problems.</P>
<P>(Both men begin laughing.)</P>
<P>Ah...The 313 in Michigan is CNA #810-424-30900.  </P>
<P>All righty....and the pin set?</P>
<P>Is 61-314.</P>
<P>PIN. What does PIN stand for?</P>
<P>Personal Identification Number.</P>
<P>Is that like private?  I dont really know.</P>
<P>Anyway, weve been having problems with data loss between CIS and the switch.</P>
<P>Ok.</P>
<P>And uh....what I need you to do is to log totally out of CIS...</P>
<P>Ok.</P>
<P>and then log back in.</P>
<P>Ok.</P>
<P>Ah... like totally out.</P>
<P>And then as you log it in, say each key as you hit it so  we can check for the ADs.</P>
<P>Ok.</P>
<P>And then let me know at what point you get out.</P>
<P>Ok.</P>
<P>I sign out of every session, right?</P>
<P>All right.  Right.</P>
<P>Ya... you see sometimes what happens a lot of times, CIS messes up when it like sends data to the switch and then someone will process phone card stuff, and the call, like they might cancel a card and the call, the switch will still put the calls  through.  We definitely do not want that happening.</P>
<P>(Sound of computer keys clicking in the background)</P>
<P>You out?</P>
<P>Ah... one more screen.</P>
<P>All right.</P>
<P>Hold on one second.....(Yells to man in background). Yes Scott, check that third trunk.  Yeh.  Its circuit ID Q3X..Right?</P>
<P>Im ready.</P>
<P>Ok.  Go ahead log back in but type slowly and say each key you hit as you hit it.</P>
<P>OK.</P>


<H4>Example #4</H4>
<P>This is  (name blanked)....may I have your area code and telephone number please?</P>
<P>Hey.........  This is Troy Corbett over at US Sprint Systems Maintenance. How ya doing?</P>
<P>Im good. </P>
<P>Ah..  need you log out of CIS and then then log right back in.</P>
<P>OK.  (Laughs)   Is there something wrong with my computer?</P>
<P>Ya... Well we think there is something wrong with the whole system so we need to check.</P>
<P>OK.  So you need me to log out of CIS...just my A frame and my E frame?</P>
<P>Thats fine.</P>
<P>Ok.  And then log back in?</P>
<P>Ummmm  but let me know when your out though.</P>
<P>Ok.  You want me to do it as we speak?</P>
<P>Please.</P>
<P>Ok.</P>
<P>(computer keys are clicking away.......)</P>
<P>Ok.  I am logged out of A.   And Im going to my E frame.</P>
<P>Ok.</P>
<P>And Im logged off E.</P>
<P>All right.</P>
<P>Ok...now I need you to log back in.  But ah do it slowly and as you do, say each key you hit before you hit so we can see that the data is passing correctly.</P>
<P>Ok.  Say that again.  As each ...Say that again..</P>
<P>Say each key ya hit right before you hit it so that we know you are hitting the key.</P>
<P>M-E-N-U   Enter</P>
<P>1 Enter  </P>
<P>Hmm</P>
<P> U-S-G -8-6-0-1 Enter</P>
<P>OK</P>
<P>My password.  You want me to spell it outloud?</P>
<P>Yeh. Just say each key as you hit it.. </P>
<P> F-E-L-E-C-I-A  </P>
<P>All right.</P>
<P>Enter,  N-A-C-L  Enter  and P-S-2.</P>
<P>All right.</P>
<P>And  CASC ... go to the main frame, and  I am in on my A screen.  I am in.</P>
<P>OK.  Ah..I dont think  hmm. .hold on..  (speaks to background).. did you guys see any data loss?</P>
<P>Hmmm.  It looks like were doing ok.   They got you guys sing your first name as passwords there?</P>
<P>No....everybody uses different ones.</P>
<P>Oh well.  Ok....You might want to change it but I guess no one is going to have access anyway.  So it really doesnt matter.  </P>
<P>I dont think they will.....</P>
<P>Ok Felecia.   How ya doing tonight?</P>
<P>Well, the calls are coming in kinda fast.  Ya think you could slow those down?</P>
<P>Ha  Ha.   I wish....  How was your Holloween? </P>
<P>Ah. I was here.</P>
<P>Hmm.</P>
<P>It was interesting to see these people walk around  in their little costumes.</P>
<P>Ya gotta watch out.  You might have people call you up and say I command you to do anything I say.. and we just...</P>
<P>And Ill say....you want me to go  home?</P>
<P>I know the feeling.  Ha  ha.  Hey Felicia,  it looks like everything is ok at CIES.  You guys have not been going into time lock.  So it looks like...</P>
<P>Well, we were earlier, but we have not been since about.... five hours ago.</P>
<P>All right.  I guess thats because everything slowed down.</P>
<P>Ok.</P>
<P>Thanks a lot for your help though. </P>
<P>Have a great evening.</P>
<P>Ok.</P>


<H4>Example #5</H4>
<P>Is there anyway for me to verify your from the Irvine office?</P>
<P>Hmm. Ah. No..Well, how may people do you know that know about CSB, BSG, and CIS.?</P>
<P>Well, I knows some people that knows about it.</P>
<P>Well, listen, I dont know that many people that care about data loss, so...</P>
<P>But your in Irvine, California?</P>
<P>Hmm Hmm..</P>
<P>What is your phone number there?</P>
<P>408-246-9970...hmmmm</P>
<P>And your name?</P>
<P>Ron Corbett.</P>
<P>Ok Ron.  Hold on...ok?</P>
<P>All right.</P>


