<!-- Article Body Table ---------------------------------------------->

<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<img border=0 width=43 height=43 src="../../images/question.gif">
</td>
<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h3>
DoctrineLINK<BR>
</h3>
<h4>

the most comprehensive online guide to military doctrine
currently available.

</h4>


</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>

<P>  
Thank you to John Pike. <a href="MAILTO:johnpike@fas.org">johnpike@fas.org</a><BR>
<BR>
DoctrineLINK is<BR>

<a href="http://www.fas.org/man/doctrine.htm">http://www.fas.org/man/doctrine.htm</a><BR>

<P>Doctrinal resources are widely scattered across the net, and they are
brought together here for the first time. This guide provides pointers
to both sites that are primary sources of doctrinal and related
publications and the capstone doctrinal publications of the Defense
Department and Military Services.

<P>We also maintain local specialized libraries of doctrinal and related
publications on several topics of current interest. </P>

   Military Space Doctrine<BR>
   <a href="http://www.fas.org/spp/military/docops/doctrine/">http://www.fas.org/spp/military/docops/doctrine/</a><BR>

   Intelligence and Security [including computer] Doctrine<BR>
   <a href="http://www.fas.org/irp/doddir/">http://www.fas.org/irp/doddir/</a><BR>

   Ballistic Missile Defense Doctrine<BR>
   <a href="http://www.fas.org/spp/starwars/docops/doctrine.htm">http://www.fas.org/spp/starwars/docops/doctrine.htm</a><BR>

<P>These local libraries of roughly 1000 documents include some 20 MB of files,
almost all in HTML. These are searchable at our site, unlike the legacy
implementations, which are too often in WPD or PDF or some other format
which complicates online viewing.</P>



John Pike<BR>
Director, Space Policy Project<BR>
Federation of American Scientists<BR>
307 Massachusetts Ave. NE<BR>
Washington, DC 20002<BR>
V 202-675-1023,   F 202-675-1024,  <a href="http://www.fas.org/">http://www.fas.org/</a><BR>


<BR>

</td>

<td width=80>
<br>
</td>
</tr>
