</tr>
</table>
<br>
<IMG ALT="[Bomb2]" SRC="../../images/bomb2_li.gif" width=580><p>


<!-- Article Body Table ---------------------------------------------->

<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<img border=0 width=43 height=43 src="../../images/question.gif">
</td>
<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h2>
  Form to Retrieve White House Publications</a>

</h2>


</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>

<P>  
This form allows you to search and retrieve White House documents on
the basis of their electronic publication dates and their categories.

<P>Overview:  This computer-generated form allows you to find documents
published between certain dates according to the categories for the
document. After you submit this form, the mail server will process your
search and return to you another form containing the matching documents.
To obtain the actual documents, you will need return the second form
after selecting the documents of interest.

<P>For best results, please try to answer the questions using the narrowest
time period and the most precise category specification.  This will
produce faster turn around time and a smaller number of documents.

<P>The categories used in this form are the same ones used to distribute
documents.  A brief listing of the categories is provided in this form,
but if you want a more precise search, you may wish to obtain the
detailed explanation of the categories, available on the ROOT
form or via the subject line command, SEND CATEGORIES.

<P>This form provides services based on your answers to a series of
questions.  Each question has instructions explaining what it does and
the valid responses. Normally, you need to answer only those questions
related to the specific service that you want.  After the valid
responses, each question has a prompt, which is a series of CAPITALIZED
WORDS surrounded by arrows. Do NOT erase these important symbols,
because the computer needs them to recognize your answer.  Please type
your selection from the valid responses immediately after the second
arrow at each prompt.  Unless otherwise indicated, your responses should
be on the same line as the prompt.  In most questions, answers are case
insensitive, and multiple choices are delimited by spaces or commas.

<P>After you have filled out the form, mail it back to the publications
mail server that automatically processes your requests:</P>

		   Publications@Research.AI.MIT.EDU<BR>
<BR>
                         --------------------<BR>

PLEASE DO NOT DELETE THE NEXT LINE!<BR>
=>FORM=> RETRIEVE-DOCUMENTS<BR>

<P>1.  Inclusion Categories: Please select some categories that each document
you want must satisfy.  </P>
<PRE>
Choices: 

  Agriculture                Alabama                    
