  Western-Europe             Wisconsin                  
  World-Order                Wyoming                    
</PRE>
<BR>
Valid Response: Categories separated by commas.<BR>
=>INCLUDE-DOCUMENTS=><BR>

<P>2.  Exclusion Categories: Please select some categories from the choices for
inclusion categories that each document you want must NOT satisfy.</P>

Valid Response: Categories separated by commas, or leave blank.<BR>
=>EXCLUDE-DOCUMENTS=><BR>

<P>3.  Document Limit: If you provide a limit, you will receive all the most
recent documents upto that number.</P>

Valid Response: An integer or leave blank.<BR>
=>DOCUMENT-LIMIT=><BR>

<P>4.  Documents After: Please specify the earliest publication date the
documents you want.</P>

Valid Response: a date (yyyy-mm-dd)<BR>
=>DOCUMENTS-AFTER=>1993-01-20<BR>

<P>5.  Documents Before: Please specify the last publication date for the
documents you want.</P>
<BR>
Valid Response: a date (yyyy-mm-dd)<BR>
=>DOCUMENTS-BEFORE=><BR>

                         --------------------<BR>

<P>This is an experimental version of the White House Public Access Email
service.  Over time, this experimental service will evolve to offer
additional capabilities.

<P>The White House Communications Service is an experiment operated at the
Massachusetts Institute of Technology with support from the Advanced
Research Projects Agency.  The service seeks to facilitate electronic
discussion of national policy, and to study the use of electronic mail
and computer networks as a component of public access to government.

Intelligent Information Infrastructure Project<BR>
M.I.T. Artificial Intelligence Laboratory<BR>


