<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h2>
 50 Fascinating URL's Gathered<BR> 
by Gary Gach <a href="MAILTO:ggg@well.com">ggg@well.com</a>

</h2>


</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>

<P>   This year I had the honor to be an invited speaker at the 50th annual 
Asilomar Conference of the World Affairs Council.  This year's topic: 
"Hard Copy" or Hard News? - Media & Foreign Affairs.

<P>I gave a guided tour of the Internet, "live," followed by some very 
lively Q&A.  I've appended the 50 Urls from my hand-out as being of 
possible interest to some members of this list:

<P>... some think tanks, Rick Smolan's recent experiment in multimedia 
publishing (24 Hours in Cyberspace ~ now out as a book with an
enhanced CD-ROM), some megasite jumpstations, news feeds, web zines,
news paperless, Howard Frederick's Communications class' home page
at Emerson College, etc.

<P>Oh, and by the way, if you're ever at Asilomar, (Pacific Coast), 
I *highly* recommend their regular "Nature Walk with Ranger."
           </P>
V i s u a l i z e     w o r l d     p e a c e !<BR>
<BR>
{tear here:}<BR>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<BR>
<BR>
50 URLS FOR WAC.ASILOMAR.50<BR>
<BR>
1.  WORLD AFFAIRS COUNCIL <BR>
<a href="http://blue.synergylabs.com/gaianet/wac">http://blue.synergylabs.com/gaianet/wac</a><BR>
<BR>
2.  FREEDOM FORUM<BR>
<a href="http://www.freedomforum.org/">http://www.freedomforum.org/</a>
<BR>
3.  POYNTER INSTITUTE<BR>
<a href="http://www.nando.net/prof/poynter/home.html">http://www.nando.net/prof/poynter/home.html</a><BR>
<BR>
4.  SHORENSTEIN CENTER<BR>
<a href="http://ksgwww.harvard.edu/~presspol">http://ksgwww.harvard.edu/~presspol</a><BR>
<BR>
5.  INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS NET<BR>
(An excellent compilation)<BR>
<a href="http://www.pitt.edu/~ian/ianres.html">http://www.pitt.edu/~ian/ianres.html</a><BR>
<BR>
6.  24 HOURS IN CYBERSPACE<BR>
<a href="http://www.cyber24.com">http://www.cyber24.com</a><BR>
<BR>
7.  NET ACROSS THE WORLD<BR>
<a href="http://netday.iworld.com/business/NATW.html">http://netday.iworld.com/business/NATW.html</a><BR>
