<h4>Credit Reporting Agencies</h4>

Trans Union, Consumer Relations Center<BR>
208 South Market<BR>
Wichita, Kansas  67202<BR>
800-879-2674<BR>
<BR>
TRW, National Consumer Assistance Center<BR>
PO Box 749029<BR>
Dallas, Texas  75374<BR>
800-392-1122<BR>
<BR>
CBI Equifax Credit Information Services<BR>
PO Box 740256<BR>
Atlanta, Georgia  30374<BR>
800-879-4094<BR>
<BR>
For credit repair, make sure you go to all three companies, not just the first one that responds.  These guys' computers don't talk to each other - they're competitors.   You have clear rights under the Fair Credit Reporting Act.  <P>


<H4>Hacker Meetings</h4>
 
PumpCon - Philadelphia, October.  Raided for two straight years. Information circulated on the net a few months prior<BR>
<BR>
SummerCon - The famous yearly private hacker gathering. Invitation only.  
<a href="MAILTO:summercon@stormking.com.">Mail for Summercon Info</A><BR>
<BR>
HoHo Con - Texas, December.  The largest, the wildest hacker con we've got.  
<a href="MAILTO:hohocon@zero.cypher.com">Info on HoHoCon</A><BR>
<BR>
DefCon - Las Vegas, Summer.  More organized than the rest, the grand daddy pof hacker cons. <a href="http://www.defcon.org">DefCon Web Site and Mailing List</A><BR>
<BR>
You owe it to yourself and your company to check these out.  Outrageous, anarchistic, chock full of information.  See how the other side lives by getting one on one with the underground. <P>
 
2600 Hacker Meetings - First Friday of every month at the following locations.  Everyone is invited - hackers to professionals to law enforcement to those without a clue.
<P>
2600 Enterprises<BR>
PO Box 99<BR>
Middle Island, New York 11953-0099<BR>
516-751-2600<BR>
