<LI><a href="http://www.stl.nps.navy.mil/c4i/">Naval Postgraduate School (The): Joint C4I Systems curriculum</A>
<BR>

<LI><a href="http://www.army.mil/disc4-pg/disc4.html-ssi">Office of the Director of C4I (Information Systems for Command, Control, Communications, and Computers</A>
<BR>

<LI><a href="http://www.seas.gwu.edu/student/reto/infowar/info-war.html-ssil">Reto E. Haeni's Information Warfare Home Page</a>
<BR>

<LI><a href="http://vislab-www.nps.navy.mil/~sdjames/info_war.html-ssil">S.D. James' Information Warfare Home Page</A>
<BR>

<LI><a href="http://www.dtic.dla.mil/airforcelink/pa/factsheets/Air_Intelligence_Agency.html-ssil">U.S. Air Force Air Intelligence Agency</A>
<BR>

<LI><a href="http://fotlan5.fotlan.army.mil/..ADMP/adotoc.html-ssi">U.S. Army Digitization Master Plan</A>
<BR>

<LI><a href="http://www.brl.mil/EA/ARL_homepage.html-ssil">U.S. Army Research Laboratory</a>
<BR>

<LI>The Joint Chiefs of Staff /Joint Doctrine Home Page for general access. This is a fine site with lots of information, as well as access to the Joint Electronic Library <a href="http://www.dtic.mil/doctrine/index.html-ssil"> The Joint Chiefs of Staff</A>
.<BR>

<LI><a href="http://www.senate.gov/~gov_affairs/">Government Affairs Office</a>

<LI><a href="http://www.nrl.navy.mil/code.5000.html-ssil">U.S. Navy Warfare Systems and Sensors ResearchDirectorate</A>
<BR>

<LI><a href="http://www.elsevier.com/ElsevierHome.html-ssil">Email Elsevier</A> For information on a number of security publications from England.<BR>
<BR>

<LI>A new Public-Key Encryption Scheme? Taking on the giant RSA? A new patent pending PK system has just been announced and the New Zealand inventors claim it offers vast improvements over the current 
methods. For more informaton on RPK Encryption scheme. Check out their claims about export control, too. <a href="http://crypto.swdev.co.nz"> http://crypto.swdev.co.nz</a><BR>
<BR>



