</td>
<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h3>
 ASSOCIATION OF OLD CROWS (AOC)<BR> INTELLIGENCE SUPPORT TO<BR> EW CONFERENCE POC December 16-17, 1996<BR>

</h3>

</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>

<BR>
12 November 1996
<BR>

<BR>

  Heading HD:  SPECIAL NOTICES<BR>
     Date DA:  November 13, 1996<BR>
<P> Contents CO:  ASSOCIATION OF OLD CROWS (AOC) INTELLIGENCE SUPPORT TO EW
               CONFERENCE POC: Association of Old Crows (AOC) Convention
               Department (703) 549-1600. 
             <P> The Association of Old Crows (AOC)
               will conduct the third 90K of its highly successful
               Intelligence Support to the EW Conference on December 16-17,
               1996, at the Defense Intelligence Analysis Center, Bolling AFB,
               Washington DC. The theme of the conference will be
               ``Intelligence and Electronic Warfare in Information Warfare.''
               The chairman of the conference will be Arthur A. Zuehlke,
               Chief, Transnational Warfare Group, Directorate for
               Intelligence Production, Defense Intelligence Agency. 
               <P>The
               keynote speaker will be Frank B. Horton III, Principal Deputy
               ASD (C31), Office of the Secretary of Defense. 
               <P>Speakers will include: </P>
               Lt Gen Kenneth Minihan, USAF, Director, National
               Security Agency; <BR>Lt Gen Albert Edmonds, USAF, Director, Defense
               Information Systems Agency; <BR>Richard Haver, Central Intelligence
               Agency; <BR>Maj Gen James Jaeger, USAF, J2, ACOM; <BR>Maj Gen Michael
               Hayden, USAF, Commander, USAF Air Intelligence Agency; <BR>Dr.
               Marvin Langston, Dept Assistant Secretary of Navy
               (C4I/EW/Space); <BR>Dr.  John O'Hara, Deputy Chief Scientist,
               National Security Agency; <BR>John Manclark, Dep Dir, USAF T&E; <BR>Col
               K. K. Dumm, Cdr, NAIC; <BR>William Swart, Technical Director,
               JC2WC; <BR>Karyn Wagner, House Permanent Select Committee on
               Intelligence; <BR>Kevin Riehle, Federal Bureau of
               Investigation. 
               <P>Among the topics to be presented are: defining
               the threat, naval developments, Air Force EW testing, USAF GDIP
               Intel Spt to IW/EW, threat technology trends, intelligence
               budget, IW in the communications architecture, IW/EW trends, IW
               from a targeting perspective, targeting and advanced warfare,
               ultrawide-band technology, C4ISR crisis support, foreign
               espionage, technical issues for intelligence/EW and IW, Chinese
               IW activities, foreign espionage, a congressional view, and a
               closing briefing, ``Is Traditional EW Still Relevant?'' 
               <P>The conference will be at the TS/SI/TK, US-Only classification
               level and is the most comprehensive forum yet undertaken -
               in-depth and at the proper classification level - to address
               issues and relationships regarding intelligence support to EW.
               For further information call the AOC Convention Department at
               (703) 549-1600.</P>

______________________________________________________________<BR>
Dr. Myron L. Cramer &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  | Principal Research Scientist<BR>
Georgia Tech Research Institute (GTRI)  | Voice: (404) 894-7292<BR>
400 Tenth Street, Room 554B&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;| FAX :  (404) 894-8636<BR>
Georgia Institute of Technology   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;     |<BR>
Atlanta, Georgia  30332-0840&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | <a href="MAILTO:myron.cramer@gtri.gatech.edu">myron.cramer@gtri.gatech.edu</a><BR>
