<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<img border=0 width=43 height=43 src="../../images/happy.gif">
</td>
<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h3>
  A great new business opportunity.

</h3>


</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>


<P>	Start up a new company to fix the Year 2000 problem for other companies.

<P>	Offer a 110% one year money back guarantee to fix your customers Year 2000 problem.  For a mere $200,000 US, your customers Year 2000 problem will go away.  If your customer is not satisfied, refund them $220,000 US! <g> 

<P>	What better way to peruse a companys information systems!  Not only do you get to look at all the information, but all the source code as well.  How many companies are buying the services of others companies to fix their Year 2000 problems?  Have any of these companies thought about the security issues of letting a third party access to all their computer systems?

<P>	Now your information can be stolen without anyone having to break-in or social engineer their way into your company.  You just hired someone to fix the Year 2000 problem and possible steal your information.

<P>	I am sure someone has thought of this before, if not, someone will.  The information your company has must be worth more than $220,000 US!
</P>

Disclaimer:<BR>
<P>	These thoughts are my own and do not reflect the thoughts or policies of my employer, Lockheed Martin, the Marshal Space Flight Center (MSFC) or NASA.</P>

<CENTER>Boyd Hawkins<BR>
               205-544-2902<BR>
               boyd.hawkins@msfc.nasa.gov<BR>
</CENTER>

<BR>

</td>

<td width=80>
<br>
</td>
</tr>
