<td valign=middle width=440>
<center>
<h3>
INFORMATION DOMINANCE FOR THE <BR>FORWARD DEPLOYED WARRIOR<BR>
</h3>
<h4>Call for Papers<BR>

</h4>
<BR>

</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>

20 November 1996<BR><BR>

<P>The Naval Command, Control and Ocean Surveillance Center, Research,
Development, Test And Evaluation Division (NRaD) and the San Diego Chapter
of AFCEA (Armed Forces Communications And Electronics Association) are
soliciting unclassified papers.  Appropriate topics in C4ISR technology in
support of the forward deployed warrior include but are not limited to:</P>

<PRE>
*  OPERATIONAL PERSPECTIVES	
 
    CJTF
    Marine Expeditionary Force
    Component Commanders
    Amphibious Ready Group
    Carrier  Battle Group
    Fleet Commanders

*  AN INTEGRATED VISION OF C4ISR 
    
    Joint Missile Defense
    The Challenge of Operating a JTF Afloat, 
     Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance
     Defense Information Infrastructure

*  C4ISR TOOLS TO MEET THE CHALLENGE
    
    Sensor to Shooter Architecture
    Tools for Joint Warfare
    Global Connectivity
    Consistent land/sea/air/space Operational Picture
    Instant information for the Warrior,
    Modeling and Simulation in Support of Warrior Training
    Human Computer Interaction


*  WARRIOR INVOLVEMENT IN ACQUISITION

    Streamlined Acquisition Initiatives/Successes 
    Joint Training Analysis and Simulation
    JWID Lessons Learned and Plans
    Advanced Concept Technology Demonstrations
    Service Battle Centers Concepts and Implementation  
    Joint Battle Center Concepts and Implementation

</PRE>
<P>Deadline for one-page abstract is 15 February 1997.  

<P>For more information please contact Dr. Robert Kolb at (619) 553-3010, Fax:
(619) 553-5188, email:  <a href="MAILTO:kolbrc@nosc.mil">kolbrc@nosc.mil</a> or Jane Renninger at (619) 592-3709, Fax:  (619) 592-4228, email:  <a href="MAILTO:jane_renninger@smtp.rc.trw.com">ane_renninger@smtp.rc.trw.com</a>.  Send postal
correspondence to AFCEA San Diego, P.O. Box 80666, San Diego, CA 92138-0666.	</P>



</td>

