<HTML>
<!--
Author:	Infowar.Com
-->
<HEAD><TITLE>

IBIS (International Banking and Information Security) Conference

</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffFF">


<!-- Header/Nav-Bar Table -------------------------------------------->

<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td valign=top width=48>
<a href="callfor.html-ssi"><img width=48 height=68 border=0 src="../../images/back.gif" alt="Back"></a>
</td>
<td valign=top width=48>
<a href="http://www.infowar.com/index.html-ssi"><img width=48 height=68 border=0 src="../../images/home.gif" alt="Home"></a>
</td>
<td valign=top width=48>
<a href="http://www.infowar.com/search_reg.html-ssi"><img width=48 height=68 border=0 src="../../images/srch.gif" alt="Search"></a>
</td>
<td valign=top align=right width=236>
<img border=0 width=236 height=68 src="../../images/line.gif">
</td>

<td width=200>
<img vspace=3 border=0 src="../../images/dot_spac.gif"><br>
<A HREF="http://www.infowar.com/sponsors/sponsors.html-ssi
"><img width=200 height=68 border=0 src="http://www.infowar.com/sponsors/ad6.gif"></A>
</td>
</tr>
</tr>
</table>
<br>
<IMG ALT="[Bomb2]" SRC="../../images/bomb2_li.gif" width=580><p>


<!-- Article Body Table ---------------------------------------------->

<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<img border=0 width=63 height=43 src="papers.gif">
</td>
<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h2>


</h2>
<B>
IBIS (International Banking and <BR>
Information Security) Conference<BR>
New York City,<BR>
February 26-28, 1997<BR>
</B>

<BR>
</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>


<P>The IBIS Conference exclusively concentrates on Security issues that 
are of concern to us all: Banking and financial transactions; on-line
commerce; security training, awareness, management; policy; law enforcement; government 
interests; national security, and so on. The IBIS Conference will 
operate four separate tracks, one of which will be dedicated to "Basics of 
Information Security For The Non-Technician."

<P>Interested US and foreign individuals, corporations, vendors, government 
agencies and academia are invited to submit papers and/or concept papers for 
presentation on topics including, but not limited to: Banking Experiences and 
Lessons Learned; Selling Staff on Security Cooperation; Process Management 
Exercises That Work; Standards ; Combatting TransNational Financial Criminals; 
Legal issues; Cryptography; Auditing: Malicious Data Diddling; Policy 
Development; Assurance Program; Protecting Critical Financial
Infrastructure and National Security; Defending Against Economic Espionage;
Moving Money Safely; Enterprise Security Models for Finance; Secure Trading From Home;
Protection in the Age of Electronic Conflict; Forensics of Financial Computer Crime ; The 
Hacker/Underground and Social Engineering; Enforcing Domestic and
International Computer Crime; The Financial Internet Under Attack; Anonymous Global Banking; 

<P>Please submit papers on these or other related issues that will of interest to 
an international financial audience. 
<BR>
---------------------------------------------------<BR>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI> Please submit papers in English as an Attachment in Word 2.0 for Windows,
(or other popular WP format) or Powerpoint. Please do not send long files,
10K, as body text in email. Hard copy submissions are also accepted. 

	<LI>For concept papers, please format them as follows: Introduction, Body, 
Summary, and What The Audience Will Learn. 

	<LI>If you are interested in chairing a Panel, please submit your concept 
for the panel, and suggested members.

	<LI>All submissions should be accompanied by a biography of the authors.

	<LI>If your proposed presentation is other than a paper, (ie, multi-media, 
interactive, etc.) please provide as much detail as possible. 

	<LI>If your submission is accepted, you will be asked to provide the 
complete version in both hard copy and electronic formats.

	<LI>Papers will be accepted through October 15, 1996, and notification of
acceptance will be no later than October 31, 1996.
</UL>
More Info: <BR>
NCSA:  717-258-1816<BR>
  <a href="MAILTO:conference@ncsa.com">conference@ncsa.com</a><BR>
  <a href="MAILTO:sponsor@ncsa.com">sponsor@ncsa.com</a><BR>
-----------------------------------------------------<BR>
<BR>
Please send your submissions to:<BR>
<BR>
<a href="MAILTO:Betty@Infowar.Com">Betty@Infowar.Com</a><BR>
or, snail mail to:<BR>
<BR>
Betty O'Hearn<BR>
Interpact, Inc.<BR>
11511 Pine St.<BR>
Seminole, FL  33772<BR>
V: 813.393.6600<BR>
F: 813.393.6361<BR>
<BR>


<BR>

</td>

<td width=80>
<br>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
