<HEAD><TITLE>

Call for papers for SOLDIER-SCHOLAR

</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffFF">


<!-- Header/Nav-Bar Table -------------------------------------------->

<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td valign=top width=48>
<a href="callfor.html-ssi"><img width=48 height=68 border=0 src="../../images/back.gif" alt="Back"></a>
</td>
<td valign=top width=48>
<a href="http://www.infowar.com/index.html-ssi"><img width=48 height=68 border=0 src="../../images/home.gif" alt="Home"></a>
</td>
<td valign=top width=48>
<a href="http://www.infowar.com/search_reg.html-ssi"><img width=48 height=68 border=0 src="../../images/srch.gif" alt="Search"></a>
</td>
<td valign=top align=right width=236>
<img border=0 width=236 height=68 src="../../images/line.gif">
</td>

<td width=200>
<img vspace=3 border=0 src="../../images/dot_spac.gif"><br>
<A HREF="http://www.infowar.com/sponsors/ad1/oss96.html-ssi
"><img width=200 height=68 border=0 src="http://www.infowar.com/sponsors/ad1.gif"></A>
</td>
</tr>
</tr>
</table>
<br>
<IMG ALT="[Bomb2]" SRC="../../images/bomb2_li.gif" width=580><p>


<!-- Article Body Table ---------------------------------------------->

<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<img border=0 width=63 height=43 src="papers.gif">
</td>
<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h2>
SOLDIER-SCHOLAR

</h2>
<B>
</B>

<BR>
</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>


<P>SOLDIER-SCHOLAR is a bi-annual journal of contemporary military
thought  published by the Military Art and Science faculty at the US Air
Force  Academy.  We are currently seeking paper submissions for our
Fall 1996  issue focusing on Warfare in the Information Age.  As
highlighted in the  President's 1996 National Security Strategy of
Engagement and Enlargement,  "the threat of intrusions to our military
and commercial information  systems poses a significant risk to
national security." We would like to  publish papers discussing both
offensive and defensive issues, and we hope  to examine not only
emerging technologies, but also the strategies  currently in
development which will use those technologies.

<P>Please consider the following when submitting papers:
<UL>
<LI>1. Articles should ideally be 2000-4000 words in length, though 
submissions of all lengths will certainly be considered.
<LI>2. Papers on topics other than the main theme may also be published;
you  are welcome to submit articles on other subjects.   
<LI>3. Please submit 3 copies of your paper which do not include the author's 
name or any other identification.  Additionally, a brief synopsis of your 
thesis and main points is requested on a separate sheet.   
<LI>4. Please also send a computer file copy, using a format which can be read  by
Microsoft Word 6.0.   
<LI>5. All articles are subject to editing and proofs will not be sent to the  authors prior to publication.  
<LI>6. Deadline for article submission: 15 October 1996 
</UL>
<P>If you have questions about this issue in particular, or
SOLDIER-SCHOLAR  in general, please direct them to:
	
34th Education Squadron<BR>
2354 Fairchild Drive, Suite 6A6<BR>
USAF Academy, CO  80840-6264<BR>
Attn: Soldier-Scholar<BR>
(719) 333-3255<BR>
DSN 333-3255<BR>
E-mail: <a href="MAILTO:Soldier_Scholar.34edg@usafa.af.mil">Soldier_Scholar.34edg@usafa.af.mil</a><BR>

Thank you very much.<BR>
  Capt William Thomas<BR>
  Editor, SOLDIER-SCHOLAR<BR>

</td>

<td width=80>
<br>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<br>
