<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h3>



<B>
Position: IT Security Director<BR>
</B>
</h3>
<BR>
</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>
<BR>
07 November 1996<BR>
<BR>
From: Dani Vicanovic <daniv@nycor.com><BR>
To: Winn@InfoWar.com<BR>
Subject: <BR>

<P>Greetings,

<P>I am hoping you will allow me to pick your brain for a position that I am
recruiting for with a client of mine who is a Fortune 500 company in
Indiana.  My name is Dani Vicanovic and I am a Technical Recruiter with a
38 year old search firm in MN.  My client is looking for an IT Security
Director and I have included a job description below.  If you know of
anyone who may be interested or could refer me to others, I would
appreciate the opportunity to talk with you.  


<P><B>Here's the job description:</B>

<P>IT Security Director:
<P>Reports to: Director, Corporate Security

<P><B>Would Prefer:</B>
<P> - 8+ years IS experience.
<P> - CISSP highly desirable (Certified Information Systems Security 
    Professional).

<P><B>Candidate Skills:</B>
<P>-  Demonstrated strong program management skills
<P>-  Demonstrated skills in development and rollout of corporate training
   and awareness programs.
<P>-  Deal well with senior management
<P>-  Excellent written communication skills
<P>-  Experience with protection of intellectual property
<P>-  Demostrated risk management skills
<P>-  Technical skills in UNIX, LAN, WAN, Internet
<P>-  LAN/WAN experience
<P>-  Substantial experience and demonstrated success in information 
    security in distributed client server environment, computer security,
    and network security architecture.

<P><B>Job Accountabilities:</B>
<P>-  Promote corporate awareness of IT Security
<P>-  Establish and maintain a global program for Corporate IS
<P>-  Provide training and guidance to all levels of the corporation
<P>-  Develop and articulate best practice, policies/procedures
<P>-  Assist in developing network security architecture
<P>-  Identify security weaknesses using diagnostic tools and develop
   solutions
<P>-  Focus on corporate global prgrams for the protection of intellectual
   property.

<P>The position is in Indiana...my client will pay all relocation expenses. 
Please forward this to anyone that you think might be interested and
have them contact me or forward resume to:</P>

Dani Vicanovic<BR>
The NYCOR Group<BR>
4930 West 77th Street #300<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55435<BR>
612-831-6444<BR>
612-835-2883<BR>
